Find the greatest common divisor of $40304$ and $30203$.
inference:
**Step 1: Find the prime factorizations of $40304$ and $30203$.**

$$40304 = 2^3 \cdot 11 \cdot 17 \cdot 23$$

$$30203 = 7 \cdot 11 \cdot 17 \cdot 29$$

**Step 2: Identify the common prime factors.**

The common prime factors are $11$ and $17$.

**Step 3: Calculate the product of the common prime factors.**

$$11 \cdot 17 = 187$$

**Final Answer: \\boxed{$187$}. I hope it is correct.**
ground_truth:
By the Euclidean Algorithm: \begin{align*}
\text{gcd}(40304, 30203) &= \text{gcd}(40304-30203, 30203) \\
&= \text{gcd}(10101, 30203) \\
&= \text{gcd}(30203-2\cdot10101, 10101) \\
&= \text{gcd}(10001, 10101) \\
&= \text{gcd}(10101 - 10001, 10001) \\
&= \text{gcd}(100, 10001) \\
&= \text{gcd}(10001 - 100\cdot100, 100) \\
&= \text{gcd}(1, 100) \\
\end{align*}Therefore, the greatest common divisor of $40304$ and $30203$ is $\boxed{1}$
